        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:32PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 231 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Natural Well, or near Neola, moving southeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Covington...
Clifton Forge...
Hot Springs...
Lake Moomaw...
Douthat State Park...
Natural Well...
and Selma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
